<title>USA: Rohm &amp; Haas names Brad Bell to replace CFO.</title>
<headline>Rohm &amp; Haas names Brad Bell to replace CFO.</headline>
<dateline>PHILADELPHIA 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Rohm and Haas Co said Monday its board elected Brad Bell as vice president.  Bell, 44, will become chief financial officer this summer after Fred Shaffer, 64, reaches mandatory retirement age, it said.</p>
<p>Bell joined Rohm and Haas last week from Whirlpool Corp where he was vice president and treasurer, the company said.</p>
<p>Bell is a graduate of the University of Illinois and the Harvard University masters in business administration program, it said.</p>
